 other branches of advanced physics. Avoiding unnecessary technical details and calculations, Electrodynamics will serve both as a useful supplemental text for graduate and advanced undergraduate students and as a helpful overview for physicists who specialize in other fields.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 29. Jun 2022) 7aSCIENCE / General.2bisacsh  aphysics, fields, space, spacetime, electrodynamics, charged particles, matter, lagrangian formalism, advanced, undergraduate, graduate, higher education, academia, textbook, reference, maxwells equations, magnetostatic, electrostatic, waves, ferromagnets, harmonic field, radiation, cosmic superluminal sources, science, big bang, nonfiction, synchrotron emission, particle acceleration, alfven wave, magnetohydrodynamics, green function.40uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9780226788449423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9780226788449/original  aGBV-deGruyter-alles